<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JUL 93 / Observer: Neighbours
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
'Is Charlie in?' asked the morning caller as the door was opened to him by a
sad-faced woman. 'You mustn't have heard,' she faltered. 'Soon after he came
in from the pub last night, he collapsed and died.'
The visitor staggered. 'I'm terribly sorry,' he said. 'Were you with him
when it happened?' The widow nodded.
'Well, did he say anything about lending me a tin of red paint?'
</TEXT>
