<HEADLINE>
FT  13 JUL 93 / Independence call on school funding
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE Association of Teachers and Lecturers yesterday called for the funding
of schools to be independent of the Department for Education.
Mr Peter Smith, the association's general-secretary, wants the new Funding
Agency for Schools to be given a guarantee of independence. He said the
plans for a common funding formula would 'represent a serious lack of
accountability for the system'.
Consultation with members in both grant-maintained and local authority
schools had shown that the department was 'already overwhelmed under the
present pace and scope of the government reforms'.
