cost of Pounds 5.5m a year.
The announcement was made by Mr Ron Neil, managing director of regional
broadcasting, on the eve of this year's Radio Academy Festival in
Birmingham.
Mr Neil said the money, part of a Pounds 40m package of investments in
programmes across all radio and television this year, had been funded
entirely from savings.
The jobs, to be advertised internally and externally, are made up of:
41 new regional bi-media radio and television correspondents in areas such
as health and education.
90 extra news producer posts deployed across the BBC's 39 local radio
stations.
A new researcher post on every local radio station to improve planning.
