<HEADLINE>
FT  12 JUL 93 / Observer: Bargain issue
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Somewhat misunderstanding the recent reports that people wanting to adopt
children may be charged Pounds 1,500 a time, a reader has called offering
his five sons for instant sale.
Although they're a snip at the official going-rate, he says, anyone
preferring a bulk deal could have them as a job lot for Pounds 7,000.
What's more, the youngest is only 27.
